title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return some user recognizable strings
description: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction, the labels returned are null. However, after data extraction, the labels are recognizable strings.
OB: The current behavior is that calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before extraction returns null, while after extraction it returns recognizable strings.
EB: The expected behavior is that IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should always return recognizable strings regardless of whether data has been extracted or not.
SR: To resolve this bug, the getColumnLabel() method in the IMetaData interface should be modified to always return recognizable strings.
